HEADWORD: Illusory
<hw>Il*lu"so*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>illusore</ets>.]</ety> <def>Deceiving, or tending of deceive;
fallacious; illusive; <as>as, <ex>illusory</ex> promises or
hopes</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

